cularly attracted to men, but are wary of emotional attachment with women; and others view sex with men—as opposed to women—as a more acceptable form of extramarital sexual behavior.Taking us inside the lives of straight white men who have sex with other men, Still Straight shows us that heterosexuality in rural America is not always, in fact, what it seems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGay menxIdentity. 0aHeterosexual menzUnited States. 0aMenxIdentity. 0aMen, WhitexSexual behaviorzUnited States. 0aRural gay menzUnited States. 0aRural menxSexual behaviorzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / Marriage & Family.2bisacsh  aAge.  aAging.  aBiphobia.  aBisexual erasure.  aBisexual.  aBud-sex.  aFamily.  aFriendship.  aGay.  aGender.  aHeterosexuality.  aHomophobia.  aLGBT.  aLove.  aMarriage.  aMasculinity.  aMen who have sex with men.  aMental health.  aRace.  aReligion.  aRomantic relationships.  aRural.  aSchool.  aSexuality.  aSports.  aStraight culture.  aWhiteness.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073910740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479801084423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479801084/original  a978-3-11-073910-7  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLET